{
  "texts": [
    "Each step is designed to preserve biological interpretability while taking advantage of the representational strength of pretrained protein language models.",
    "Figure 1 shows an overview of the entire pipeline.",
    "Stage I: Learning Motif Concept VectorsConstructing Windowed Training Samples.",
    "For each Pfam motif, we first construct a training dataset consisting of short subsequences (\"windows\") drawn from proteins known to contain that motif (Figure 1A).",
    "Positive windows are extracted by centering a window of length w on each annotated motif instance, where w is defined as the median annotated motif length plus a small buffer to accommodate natural variation across homologs."
  ]
}